parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective seatbelt buckle assembly can cause the buckle to break, preventing it from latching and protecting the occupant in a sudden stop or accident, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle may break or fail to latch
the seatbelt may not pull out properly
the seatbelt anchor may not work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: often without visible signs of wear on the tire surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Lock-Up and Rear Tire Lock-Up
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission lock-up and subsequent rear tire lock-up can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents and loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: the vehicle becomes difficult to control

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Rust and Water Accumulation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the fuel tank can cause rust and corrosion, leading to fuel leaks and potentially causing fires or explosions. This can also lead to engine damage and performance issues.
symptoms: soft or rusty top of fuel tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, it can also result in fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment
engine stalling or loss of power
warning lights or alarms on the dashboard.
